news.title: Otis expects its annual sales to be about $14.2 billion in FY25
news.para: Otis now expects its annual sales to be about $14.2 billion, below its prior expectation of between $14.3 billion and $14.5 billion.

news.title: United Kingdom increases stamp duty tax on second homes
news.para: "This will support over 130,000 additional transactions from people buying their first home, or moving home, over the next five years," Reeves said.

news.title: Mysuru: Enforcement directorate probe of MMG Construction's owner concludes
news.para: Jayaram, owner of MMG Construction, told reporters that officials examined his complete business records spanning 24 years, with particular focus on his firm's activities over the past 13 years.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh govt to begin registrations for Khurja Industrial Township from Nov 11
news.para: Located about 18km away from the upcoming Noida Airport, the Khurja township will revolutionise Bulandshahr's ODOP market by connecting it to global markets.

news.title: Central panel recommends environment clearance for Sipcot park near Pulicat
news.para: ​The 364 crore project spread across 280 hectares will have to implement measures to conserve and protect local biodiversity as proposed by the Salim Ali Centre for Ornithology and Natural History (SACON).

news.title: Activists accuse Bengaluru civic body for unsafe building practices
news.para: A group of volunteers has submitted a memorandum to the Karnataka Lokayukta and Upa Lokayukta, urging action to prevent unauthorised building construction following the recent collapse of an illegal multi-story building that led to the tragic death of nine workers.

news.title: Tamil Nadu CM inaugurates over 3,200 tenements of TNUHDB
news.para: The tenements are located in 12 places, including five in Chennai, two each in Coimbatore and Erode, and one each in Kanyakumari, Thanjavur and Trichy.

news.title: Noida authority asks defaulters to pay Rs 1,578 crore rent dues
news.para: The OTS-III proposal, which would have been the third such scheme, was intended to ease the financial burden on defaulters by offering relief through recalculated dues at standard interest rates, potentially reducing the outstanding balance from Rs 1,578.14 crore to Rs 751.86 crore.

news.title: Indore administration proposes hike in collector's guideline for 469 locations
news.para: During the meeting, the committee scrutinised the proposals presented by stamp and registration department regarding the increase in the guideline values for property in 112 locations by 0-10%, 190 locations by 11-20%, 77 locations by 21-30%, and 90 locations by more than 31%.

news.title: Gurugram civic body orders sealing of illegal structure constructed on housing plot
news.para: The action was taken in response to a complaint filed by a resident living on the ground floor, who alleged that another resident constructed an unauthorised structure above their floor without a sanctioned plan.

news.title: Bengaluru: FIR filed against Lactin Developers for violating sanctioned building plan
news.para: BBMP had approved a building plan for property owners G Lakshmi Prasad and D Hardeep and A Vijaykumar, partners of GPA holder Lactin Developers, in plots nos. 6 and 7 in Mallathahalli village.

news.title: Sundaram Home Finance reports Rs 44 crore net profit in Q2 FY25
news.para: For the six month period ending September 30, 2024 net profits of the company stood at Rs 111 crore as against net profits of Rs 117 crore registered a year ago.

news.title: Certus Capital invests Rs 150 crore in two residential projects in Mumbai
news.para: These mid-income housing projects near Mumbai international airport and extended western suburb of Vasai have an aggregate development of 385,000 sq ft and revenue potential of over Rs 750 crore.

news.title: Delhi court orders fresh probe in cheating case against Gautam Gambhir and others
news.para: An alleged cheating case was filed against real estate firms Rudra Buildwell Realty Pvt. Ltd, H R Infracity Pvt Ltd., U M Architectures and Contractors Ltd., and Gambhir, who was a director and brand ambassador of the companies' joint venture.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh government to penalise Amrapali Leisure Valley Developers for illegal borewells
news.para: A recent survey by the district administration found at least 50 villa owners at Amrapali Leisure Valley society have set up borewells for personal consumption.

news.title: Sebi issues demand notices to Reliance Home Finance's promoter, others in fund diversion case
news.para: The regulator has warned these entities for attachment of assets and bank accounts if they fail to make the payment within 15 days.

news.title: Homebuyers protest against Smart World Developers in Gurugram
news.para: The protesters claim that Smart World Developers began canceling units without prior consent starting in Sept 2024, with the cancellations persisting into Oct.

news.title: Sebi proposes measures to simplify public issue processes for small and medium REITs
news.para: SM REITs were introduced in March 2024 to encourage smaller real estate investments and increase participation in the sector. These are similar to REITs but operate on a smaller scale with a minimum asset value of Rs 50 crore compared to Rs 500 crore for regular REITs.

news.title: BigBloc Constructions doubles AAC blocks manufacturing capacity
news.para: Narayan Saboo, chairman, BigBloc Constructions said, "Along with this, we have also commissioned installation of 625KW rooftop solar plant at Wada facility."

news.title: Delhi CM approves 'anywhere registration' policy for property registration
news.para: Delhi residents will now be able to register their property at any sub-registrar office of their choice, at their convenience. Delhi Chief Minister Atishi has approved the 'Anywhere Registration' policy, which removes the requirement for citizens to visit a specific sub-registrar office.
